</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF9FF942FCECF869FCF0F829" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[768,868,1977,2003]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Caminus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF9FF942FCECF869FCF0F829" box="[768,868,1977,2003]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Caminus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF9FF942FC74F868FBA9F828" authorityName="Bowerbank in Johnston" authorityYear="1842" box="[920,1085,1976,2002]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Pachymatisma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF9FF942FC74F868FBA9F828" box="[920,1085,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachymatisma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B01FF9FF942FB99F868FA05F828" author="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M." box="[1141,1425,1975,2002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref28068" refString="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M. (2015) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Sponges in the Family Geodiidae (Demospongiae: Astrophorina). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir 128. National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research Ltd, Wellington, 102 pp." type="book" year="2015">Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF9FF942FF7BF80CFF62F80C" authorityName=", Sollas" authorityYear="1888" box="[151,246,2012,2038]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erylinae">Erylinae</taxonomicName>
are now defined as having short-shafted triaenes (although this is not strictly true with the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FF7BFF49FD50FF49" authority="Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly, 2015" authorityName="Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly" authorityYear="2015" box="[151,708,152,179]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Pachymatisma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="nodosa">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FF7BFF49FE01FF49" box="[151,405,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Pachymatisma nodosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B01FF98F945FE71FF49FD50FF49" author="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M." box="[413,708,152,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref28068" refString="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M. (2015) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Sponges in the Family Geodiidae (Demospongiae: Astrophorina). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir 128. National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research Ltd, Wellington, 102 pp." type="book" year="2015">Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), microrhabds in the ectocortex (outer cortex), with spherules in the ectocortex being specific to 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FE10FF6DFDF4FF2D" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[508,608,189,215]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Caminus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FE10FF6DFDF4FF2D" box="[508,608,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Caminus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and aspidasters to 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FCD9FF6DFB15FF2D" authority="(Cardenas et al. 2010)" authorityName="Cardenas" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Cardenas" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[821,1153,189,215]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FCD9FF6DFCEAFF2D" box="[821,894,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Erylus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B01FF98F945FC60FF6DFBEDFF2D" author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[908,1145,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FC11FF6EFBA2FF2D" box="[1021,1078,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36F0FF98F945FF2BFF31FC85FE29" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Although supported by molecular studies, the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FCB1FF32FC2CFF01" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[861,952,226,251]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FCB1FF32FC2CFF01" box="[861,952,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FC31FF31FBABFF01" authorityName=", Sollas" authorityYear="1888" box="[989,1087,225,251]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erylinae">Erylinae</taxonomicName>
, implies the major synapomorphies, i.e., the loss of protriaenes and anatriaenes, and the loss of sterrasters/aspidasters in 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FB4AFED5FA88FEE5" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[1190,1308,261,287]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Geodiidae</taxonomicName>
, have been secondarily lost in 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FE9CFEFAFE5FFEB9" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[368,459,298,323]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FE9CFEFAFE5FFEB9" box="[368,459,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B01FF98F945FDE4FEF9FC9CFEB9" author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[520,776,297,323]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FD95FEFAFD26FEB9" box="[633,690,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
. Similarly, inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FBF5FEFAFB35FEB9" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1049,1185,298,323]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="euastrum">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FBF5FEFAFB35FEB9" box="[1049,1185,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E. euastrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which contains aspidasters) within 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FEADFE9EFE08FE9D" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[321,412,334,359]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FEADFE9EFE08FE9D" box="[321,412,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B01FF98F945FE39FE9DFD2DFE9D" author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[469,697,333,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FDAFFE9EFDEEFE9D" box="[579,634,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
) means that there is no morphological character that can be used to definitively separate 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FE6CFEA2FE4FFE71" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[384,475,370,395]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FE6CFEA2FE4FFE71" box="[384,475,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FDF0FEA1FDF1FE71" box="[540,613,369,395]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FDF0FEA1FDF1FE71" box="[540,613,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in a practical sense (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B01FF98F945FCBCFEA1FBFAFE71" author="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M." box="[848,1134,368,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref28068" refString="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M. (2015) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Sponges in the Family Geodiidae (Demospongiae: Astrophorina). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir 128. National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research Ltd, Wellington, 102 pp." type="book" year="2015">Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly 2015</bibRefCitation>
). We question the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FF59FE46FEA8FE55" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[181,316,406,431]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="euastrum">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FF59FE46FEA8FE55" box="[181,316,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E. euastrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FE7DFE46FE78FE55" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[401,492,406,431]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FE7DFE46FE78FE55" box="[401,492,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for practical purposes, while keeping the two genera separate, and believe the more molecular evidence is needed to support these decisions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36F0FF98F945FF2BFE0DFEC6FD7D" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
In the meantime, we will continue to use the traditional, positive concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D73FF98F945FBC2FE0EFB1DFE0D" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[1070,1161,478,503]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EAE2FF98F945FBC2FE0EFB1DFE0D" box="[1070,1161,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(i.e., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B01FF98F945FB20FE0DFADAFE02" author="Uriz, M. J." box="[1228,1358,477,504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="134 - 140" refId="ref28586" refString="Uriz, M. J. (2002 b) Family Geodiidae Gray, 1867. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Soest, R. W. M. van (Eds.), Systema Porifera: A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, pp. 134 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 14" type="book chapter" year="2002">Uriz 2002b</bibRefCitation>
) to assign new species, i.e., that these are sponges with a thin crust-forming cortex composed of smooth microrhabds that may or may not be centrotylote. In addition, the species possess short- to long-shafted dichotriaenes, orthotriaenes or plagiotriaenes and oxeas as megascleres, and the microsclere complement of microxeas and microrhabds may include euasters.
</paragraph>
